<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911015-0027</DOCNO><DOCID>911015-0027.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Alpha Solarco Inc.:   Company Expects to Post   Profit for Its First Period</HL><DATE>10/15/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10</SO><CO>   ASCO</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>INDUSTRIAL TECHNOLOGY andamp; PRODUCTION, QUALITY CONTROL (ITC)</IN><NS>EARNINGS PROJECTIONS (ERP)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Alpha Solarco Inc. said it would post its first quarterlyoperating profit since it was founded in 1979, totaling about$510,000, or about one cent a share.   The Cincinnati-based maker of solar electricity systemssaid the profit for the fiscal first quarter ended Aug. 31largely reflects the successful completion of the first phaseof its joint venture with a China-based electronics companyto produce solar modules in China. Alpha Solarco said thefirst phase of the contract, a $1 million technologytransfer, was completed in September. In the year-earlierquarter, the company reported a loss of $200,952.</LP><TEXT>   The company said the first-quarter profit of $510,000includes an extraordinary tax credit of $173,000. AlphaSolarco has 42 million shares outstanding.</TEXT></DOC>